parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become loose or stuck, which can lead to inadequate protection in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt does not lock or retract properly
the seat belt will not pull out
the seat belt does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in crash situations can increase the risk of serious injury or death to vehicle occupants, as they are not provided with the intended protection.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
even with significant damage to the vehicle
occupants may experience injuries that could have been mitigated by airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden tire separation or failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: and may cause the vehicle to be extremely difficult to control.
